==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Postmeridian
<hw>Post`me*rid"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>postmeridianus</ets>; <ets>post</ets> after +
<ets>meridianus</ets>. See <er>Meridian</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Coming after the sun has passed the meridian; being in, or
belonging to, the afternoon. (Abbrev. <abbr><sc>P.
M.</sc></abbr>)</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig., belonging to the after portion of life;
late.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Post-mortem</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
